    "System.Title": "Add Management Functionality for teachers to Rostering API",
    "System.BoardColumn": "New",
    "System.BoardColumnDone": false,
    "Microsoft.VSTS.Common.StateChangeDate": "2026-04-14T10:15:51.637Z",
    "Microsoft.VSTS.Common.Priority": 2,
    "Microsoft.VSTS.Common.ValueArea": "Business",
    "Microsoft.VSTS.Scheduling.Effort": 13,
    "Custom.HiddenBehindFeatureFlag": false,
    "WEF_971899FEEDE3458F83E2EE8197341977_System.ExtensionMarker": true,
    "WEF_971899FEEDE3458F83E2EE8197341977_Kanban.Column": "New",
    "WEF_971899FEEDE3458F83E2EE8197341977_Kanban.Column.Done": false,
    "WEF_E5E41166570044F9909817F8255875AB_System.ExtensionMarker": true,
    "WEF_E5E41166570044F9909817F8255875AB_Kanban.Column": "New",
    "WEF_E5E41166570044F9909817F8255875AB_Kanban.Column.Done": false,
    "System.Description": "<div><b>User Story</b> </div><div>As a teacher </div><div>I want to add new students to the Rostering system </div><div>So that i can access their details view sittings and active logs&nbsp; </div><div><br> </div><div><br> </div><div><b>Scope</b> </div><div>This PBI focuses on the API layer for students creation.&nbsp; </div><div><br> </div><div><b>Functional Requirements</b> </div><div><ul><li>Create new students&nbsp; </li><li>Validate student data created </li><li>Verify activation email is sent </li><li>Audit log all user creation events </li> </ul> </div><div><br> </div><div><b>Technical Requirements</b> </div><div><ul><li>RESTful API endpoint: POST /api/1/students </li><li>Authorization: Admin, School Admin or teachers&nbsp; </li><li>Database: User, students, UserSchool tables </li> </ul> </div><div><br> </div><div><br> </div>",
    "Microsoft.VSTS.Common.AcceptanceCriteria": "<div><b>Acceptance Criteria</b> </div><div><br> </div><div><b>AC1: Create User with Valid Data</b> </div><div>GIVEN I am authenticated as teacher </div><div>WHEN I POST a student creation request with valid data </div><div>THEN the student is created in the database </div><div>AND the API returns 201 Created with the user details </div><div><br> </div><div><br> </div><div><b>AC2: Email Uniqueness Validation</b> </div><div>GIVEN a student already exists </div><div>WHEN I POST a user creation request with the same email </div><div>THEN the API returns 400 Bad Request </div><div>AND the error message states 'Email already exists' </div><div>AND no user is created </div><div><br> </div><div><b>AC3: Authorization Check</b> </div><div>GIVEN I am authenticated as a Teacher (non-admin) user </div><div>WHEN I POST a user creation request </div><div>THEN the API returns 403 Forbidden </div><div>AND the error message states 'Insufficient permissions' </div><div><br> </div><div><b>AC4: School Association Validation</b> </div><div>GIVEN I am a School Admin for School A </div><div>WHEN I POST a student creation request&nbsp; </div><div>THEN the API returns 403 Forbidden </div><div>AND the error message states 'Cannot create users for other schools' </div><div><br> </div><div><b>AC5: Welcome Email Sent</b> </div><div>GIVEN I POST a student creation request to welcome </div><div>WHEN the student is successfully created </div><div>THEN a welcome email is sent to the user's email address </div><div>AND the email contains the password reset link </div><div>AND the link expires in 7 days </div><div><br> </div><div><b>AC6: Input Validation</b> </div><div>GIVEN I POST a user creation request with invalid data </div><div>WHEN any required field is missing or invalid (invalid email format, empty name, invalid role) </div><div>THEN the API returns 400 Bad Request </div><div>AND the error response contains specific validation messages for each field </div><div><br> </div><div><b>AC8: Audit Logging</b> </div><div>GIVEN I successfully create a student </div><div>WHEN the operation completes </div><div>THEN an audit log entry is created with: userId, createdBy, timestamp, schoolId, role </div><div>AND the log is stored in the AuditLog table </div><div><br> </div><div><b>AC9: Idempotency</b> </div><div>GIVEN I POST the same student creation request twice within 5 minutes </div><div>WHEN the second request has an identical idempotency key </div><div>THEN the API returns the existing user (201 or 200) </div><div>AND no duplicate user is created </div><div><br> </div><div><b>AC10: Error Handling</b> </div><div>GIVEN the database is unavailable </div><div>WHEN I POST a user creation request </div><div>THEN the API returns 503 Service Unavailable </div><div>AND the error is logged </div><div>AND no partial data is committed </div>",
